Never-before-seen footage of Michael Jackson dancing
2013-06-26 05:12:15 GMT
THE waxworks museum Madame Tussauds has released never-seen-before archive footage of Michael Jackson dancing for its sculptors.It shows the singer performing some iconic dance moves for the Madame Tussauds sculptors as they attempted to create a likeness of him. While the footage is not of the best quality and is also in slow motion, it is clearly the king of pop who is recorded. Jackson died on June 25th four years ago. In the year he would of turned 55, Madame Tussauds are launching three new figures of Michael Jackson at the Lyric theatre where ‘Thriller Live’ is being staged.(Agencies)
